        The orientation chamber was larger than the intake room, its vine-walled surfaces curving into something almost like a classroom—bioluminescent patches provided steady light, and several vine-formed seats faced a flat presentation surface.

        Scout bounced into one of the vine seats and settled.

        Kira lowered herself into another seat; her leg had progressed from throbbing to a steady ache that colored everything. «How many hours until the temporary treatment wore off? How much longer until this was over?»

        A sound drew her attention—smooth mechanical rolling.

        A plant entered the chamber on a wheeled platform.

        The platform itself was remarkable: three wheels arranged for stability, built from what looked like salvaged materials but operating with impressive smoothness. A thick central stem rose from it and branched into an array of enormous flowers—each bloom easily fifteen centimeters across. The flowers were currently a pale cream color, petals fully open in an impressive display.

        Delicate tendrils extended from the main stem to manipulate a joystick embedded in the platform; the movements were precise, elegant. The whole setup rolled to the front of the chamber and came to a perfectly controlled stop.

        Florence said, "Good evening! I'm Florence. I'll be coordinating your workplace safety orientation today."

        The flowers shifted subtly—petals repositioning, color bleeding toward pale yellow.

        Kira asked, "This is... Florence?"

        Florence said, "Yes—I'm very pleased to assist with your onboarding process. Shall we begin?"

        Scout bounced once.

        Holloway said from a fruiting body near the wall, "Florence has prepared a comprehensive presentation on workplace safety fundamentals. Please give your full attention!"

        «Workplace safety.»

        Kira had crashed from space; her ship had gone down in a catastrophic systems failure. She was stranded on an alien planet. And they were going to teach her workplace safety.

        Florence said, "Let's start with proper lifting techniques—this is essential for preventing workplace injuries."

        The flowers shifted to a focused cream tone. Images appeared on the presentation surface—pressed or grown into bark—showing simplified figures in various lifting postures.

        Florence continued, "When lifting heavy objects, it's crucial to bend at the knees, not the waist. Keep your back straight, core engaged, and lift with your legs."

        Kira stared and asked, "What objects am I lifting?"

        Florence replied, "Workplace materials, of course—equipment, supplies, documentation." The flowers flickered briefly orange—confusion or concern? "The principles apply to any lifting scenario."

        Buddy interjected, sounding helpful, "You'll need to understand proper safety protocols for your new environment."
